morphospeciesIDRemarks: In this locality we have a handful of interesting putative hybrids birches. This one has two woody plant forms simultaneously. It has a shrub shape at the bottom with two emergent boles of a more tree habit. Twigs are glandular but less so than begl bena generally. Leaf size varies quite a bit on the individual with large deltoid to ovate leaves easily 3cm wide and longer. The tree form boles on the individual have leaves that are smaller and wider than long.
